HEADWORD: Hart
<hw>Hart</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>hart</ets>, <ets>hert</ets>, <ets>heort</ets>, AS.
<ets>heort</ets>, <ets>heorot</ets>; akin to D. <ets>hert</ets>, OHG.
<ets>hiruz</ets>, <ets>hirz</ets>, G. <ets>hirsch</ets>, Icel.
<ets>hj⟦oum⟧rtr</ets>, Dan. & Sw. <ets>hjort</ets>, L.
<ets>cervus</ets>, and prob. to Gr. <grk>kerao`s</grk> horned,
<grk>ke`ras</grk> horn. ⟦root⟧230. See <er>Horn</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A stag; the male of the red deer. See the Note
under <er>Buck</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Goodliest of all the forest, <qex>hart</qex> and hind.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

